					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-4731367#post-3672497</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-4731367/recovered-media:the-hard-boiled-adventures-of-murphy-law#post-3672497</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 03 Jan 2018 06:42:45 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Petrograd</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>455145</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Hello folks! So this was my <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-4296254/sixth-annual-scp-art-exchange">2017 gift exchange</a> present for The Great Hippo, concerning his ever-delightful hard-boiled metanarrative character <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/murphy-law-hub">Murphy Law</a>.</p> <p>I have a ton of attributions to get out of the way, so let's do that.<br /> None of these comics were originally drawn by me, I just did the photoshopping<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-501215-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" >1</a></sup>. All of the comic art was sourced from the following comic strips:<br /> <strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Buck Ryan</span></strong> created by Don Freeman and artist Jack Monk, retrieved from <a href="http://comicbookplus.com/?cid=3358">here</a> and <a href="http://comicbookplus.com/?dlid=69772">here</a><br /> <strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">War on Crime</span></strong> by Rex Collier and artists Kemp Sterrett and Jimmy Thompson, retrieved from <a href="http://comicbookplus.com/?cid=2335">here</a>.<br /> Both Buck Ryan and War on Crime are in the public domain. <a href="https://exhibits.stanford.edu/copyrightrenewals">I checked.</a></p> <p>Some other details were CC0 from <a href="https://pixabay.com/">Pixabay</a><br /> Daevic runes or <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-2140">SCP-2140-ML!</a> depending on your interpretation are taken from <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-2140">SCP-2140</a>, originally created with fonts by Juan Carlos Porcel from <a href="http://elderprops.tumblr.com/post/89934858272/free-fonts-necrofonticon2">http://elderprops.tumblr.com/post/89934858272/free-fonts-necrofonticon2</a>. All under CC.<br /> And the picture 7 was created using <a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/bittbox/6441607381">this image</a>, CC BY 2.0 by bittbox.<br /> Also not required for attribution, but I'm very grateful for the font <a href="https://www.fontsquirrel.com/license/VTC-Letterer-Pro">VTC Letterer Pro.</a><br /> And I linked them above, but <a href="http://comicbookplus.com/">Comic Book Plus</a>, a free collection of public domain comics and pulp novels, really saved my ass on this one. If you're into that stuff, check 'em out.</p> <p>SOME SCP'S WERE HARMED IN THE CREATION OF THIS COMIC, INCLUDING<br /> <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-3043">SCP-3043</a> by The Great Hippo<br /> <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-2740">SCP-2740</a> by djkaktus<br /> <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-738">SCP-738</a> by Le Blue Dude<br /> <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-2548">SCP-2548</a> by TyGently<br /> <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-3000">SCP-3000</a> by djkaktus, Joreth, and A Random Day<br /> <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-140">SCP-140</a> and <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-2357">SCP-2357</a> and <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-2140">SCP-2140</a> by AssertiveRoland; Communism will win; and sirpudding<br /> And <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-2747">SCP-2747</a>! (Dun dun dunnnn!) by minmin</p> <p>(Edit: And <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-423">Fred</a> and <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/operation-overmeta">Gordon</a> from DrEverettMann and Rimple. Sheesh.)</p> <p>Also I made the URL really long without really thinking about it. Edit: And forgot the rating module. Boy, I'm rusty.</p> <p>Edit edit: Annnd the clickable links for full size aren't working. I'll try to see what I can do about that tomorrow.</p> <div class="footnotes-footer"> <div class="title">Footnotes</div> <div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-501215-1"><a href="javascript:;" >1</a>. Ok, GIMPing.</div> </div> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
